@Andrzej

Lovers' Lane is where people went (and still go, I imagine) to park their cars in 1950s-70s films, stereotypically, and canoodle.  Stars like Warren Beatty and Steve Mcqueen have been spotted there on celluloid. Or, sometimes, folks even make nookie there, which is a similarly old-timey euphemism for the beast with two backs and other copulational permutations.

Usually, but not always, Lovers' Lane is located on a scenic overlook of the town from which the lovers hail, the far-off night lights and the now-distant and sleeping sources of balefull authority enhancing the sense of furtive romance.

@Vaer

A must-see film if you're into 50s Cold-War-nuclear-doomsday cinematic paranoia reels (though the film's producer vehemently denied the metaphors).

A classic of the genre.

