@Petrol Random fact about Diana. She's Diana, Princess of Wales or Lady Diana or technically Princess Charles. She was never Princess in her own name. She was a Mrs. Prince (example Princess Michael is Prince Michael's wife Maria Christine).
You are princess in your own name if you are born one or monarch creates you to be one...which almost never happens. It's not Princess Catherine or Kate for same reason. As current holder of the title she is The Princess of Wales.

Now there are some good seeds for Crossword Clues.

